<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-05-15T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-05-15T12:00:00-05:00" n="375" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d375">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">838.516/284: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Armour</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-05-15T12:00:00-05:00">May 15,
                                1934—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 12:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>47. My telegram No. 42, May 11, 1 p.m. Could a reply be expedited as the
                            President is sending the contract to the Legislature tomorrow and would
                            like to have it accompanied by the draft notes and draft treaty.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Armour</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>